Tribal rebels in southwest Pakistan killed three soldiers and injured seven in an attack on a paramilitary convoy.
Violence escalated in Baluchistan after a doctor's rape near the Sui gasfield.
Fierce gun battles between rebels and troops left up to 30 dead and 70 injured.
Thousands fled Dera Bugti as clashes intensified, with armed tribesmen surrounding the town.
The conflict also resulted in the deaths of 39 devotees at a shrine and 17 Hindus in a temple.
The situation remains tense as government officials and troops evacuate the area amid ongoing tribal unrest.
